  "general_provisions": "This bill amends provisions related to social studies instructional materials and art standards.",
  "hilighted_provisions": "This bill:<hr><ltbullet>requires the State Board of Education to develop high-quality open educational resource instructional materials for social studies and civics education;<hr><ltbullet>requires open educational resources to be updated when social studies standards are revised; <hr><ltbullet>requires social studies instruction on American Exceptionalism and comparative government systems;<hr><ltbullet>requires instruction on the Bible as a literary and historical text;<hr><ltbullet>requires integration of founding documents in English language arts assessments;<hr><ltbullet>requires instruction on the roles and responsibilities of government officials;<hr><ltbullet>allows local education agencies to determine whether applied crafts and technical arts courses meet fine arts credit requirements; and <hr><ltbullet>makes technical and conforming changes.",
